athology computer system. Tests patient samples, quality control materials and other specimens to aid physicians in the diagnosis and treatment of patient conditions. Orders and prepares reagents, supplies and materials utilized in the department(s), supervise or delegate such responsibilities. Sets up schedule of preventative maintenance for calibration and repairs of instrument and test equipment Troubleshoots equipment and procedures as needed to assure patient safety through effective accurate testing Conserves hospital resources by using equipment and supplies as needed to perform job duties. Contributes to departmental operations by performing other related duties as may be required and/or assigned. Contributes to effective customer relations by assisting patients, visitors, physicians and any other departments or outside parties to resolve expressed concerns, and by demonstrating a welcoming and helpful attitude Conforms to Memorial Medical Center strategic plan and Behavioral Standards. Supports the Mission, Vision and Values of Memorial Medical Center and strive to provide the most cost effective, accurate, and timely patient testing possible within their ability to impact workflow and decision making. Performs other related work as required or requested. The intent of this job description is to provide a representative summary of the major duties and responsibilities performed by incumbents of this job. Incumbents may be requested to perform tasks other than those specifically presented in this description. "
